# The Shared Responsibility Model

The most-quoted framing on AWS — most architecture decisions sit on it.

- **AWS** → security **of** the cloud: data centres, hardware, hypervisor, network, control planes
- **You** → security **in** the cloud: data, identity, app code, service configuration

## The line shifts by service (IaaS → serverless)

| | EC2 | RDS | S3 / Lambda |
|---|---|---|---|
| Physical / hypervisor | AWS | AWS | AWS |
| **OS patching** | **you** | AWS | AWS |
| DB / runtime patching | **you** | AWS | AWS |
| Security Group | **you** | **you** | n/a |
| **Data · IAM · config** | **you** | **you** | **you** |

**The last row never moves** — you *always* own your **data, IAM, and access**, however managed the service.
